4:
Looks like we're gonna wrap up this
year's Halloween real smoothly.
12: You think it's out for blood?
27:
Our first duel lasted a mere
moment. Not in ten or even a
hundred rounds did your blade ever
reach me!
30:
And yet, you never surrendered.
Your eyes remained focused, and
you even grew to withstand my
one-hit knockout!
34:
So... Sir Alk. Please, teach me! Teach
me through your blood...
43: I won't... take no for an answer!
56:
That girl is nuts! I'm FLYING and she
still almost took me out a couple
times!
60:
I don't know what's going on either!
Something's really off with her...
80:
Yumu! You're still alive, right?! She
didn't bite you, RIGHT?!
89:
Ignore my outfit for now. Alk, I need
your help with capturing Celtie.
93:
I don't want her to do something
she'll regret. We have to bring her
back to her senses before anyone is
harmed!
98:
So you'll be the decoy, Yumu! You
can do that... right?
107:
Sorry about this. I've got a plan in
place, so let's get moving!
111: Hey, Celtie! I know you're in there!
115: You wanna spar? Then let's spar!
119:
Heh-heh-heh... Is that what you're
thinking?
122:
This isn't about sparring. I simply
want your answer...
126:
So please, Sir Alk! Give me your
blood!
135:
Sorry, missy! We're not here to play
your game!
141: Ninja Art: Shadow Prison! Again! Now!
151:
I'm sorry... I'll fight you properly next
time.
173:
...I just wanted them to tell me... and I
just wanted them to listen.
176:
I wanted them to know what I
discovered within the light of steel
clashing against steel. I wanted to
know what they found, too.
179:
But my voice reached no one, and
the look in the eyes of anyone who
looked back at me was always
strained or distorted.
183:
...But I thought that was all right. I
would leave everything else behind
and myself become the blade...
187:
Because I knew that's how I could
come into my own.
192:
The flavor reminds you of a beauty
dancing at the ball, eh? That's...
quite a way of describing it.
197:
I-is it really so strange? The cake is
lovely, with an elegant fragrance,
yet its flavor contains a subdued
acidity...
201:
No, no. It's not strange at all. It just
seems like you have a unique way
of appreciating flavor.
204:
By the way... What did you think of
the pastries I made?
208:
They remind me of a large...
sheepdog.
221:
I wanted to become the person you
saw me as.
225:
I am Celtie! I love the blade, my
parents, and my brother!
229:
I also love cake filled with
blackcurrants and beautifully
embroidered dresses! And I
solemnly refuse to give up any of it!
232: So I'll dive into the light!
235:
I want to tell you about coming back
from the light. I want to hear you
laugh.
239:
And then I want you to tell me about
your story!
250:
...Good morning, Celtie. How are you
feeling?
254: I'm... Okay... Still feel a little funny...
258:
Oh? Guess we should continue on
like this for a while, then.
266:
Y-yeah?
I'm sweaty, so don't get too close to—
275:
HUH?!
H-hey! You still want my blood or
something?! C-cut it out!
279: Heh, heh... No. I don't want to let go.
